EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to courts; requesting that the Nevada Supreme
Court study procedures for notifying defendants and
persons who are issued a civil infraction citation of
certain information; requesting that the Nevada Supreme
Court adopt court or administrative rules governing such
procedures; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law: (1) requires a peace officer to collect a telephone number and an
2 indication of whether a person who is issued a civil infraction citation agrees to
3 receive communications by text message; and (2) authorizes a court to send certain
4 communications relating to civil infraction citations by text message. (NRS
5 484A.7035, 484A.704) This bill requests that the Nevada Supreme Court: (1) study
6 procedures for notifying defendants and persons who are issued a civil infraction
7 citation of certain information; (2) consider, without limitation, best practices, input
8 from interested stakeholders and the technological needs of the courts when
9 studying such procedures; and (3) adopt court or administrative rules governing
10 such procedures.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
